									If you don't yet read Tibetan script, begin with the <strong>Alphabet & Reading Pre-course</strong>. You'll learn to read and pronounce the script fluently; it's the reading prerequisite for Beginner 101. The pre-course runs 6 weeks with two weekly live classes and one weekly 1:1 practice session. You're also welcome to take it even if you don't plan to continue to 101.
								</p>
								<p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; color: #666;">
									If you can already read, start with <strong>Beginner 101 → Beginner 102</strong>, then continue to <strong>Intermediate 201 → 202</strong>, and finally <strong>Advanced 301 → 302</strong>. Each level builds on the one before it and follows the next volume of <em>The Heart of Tibetan Language</em>.
								</p>
